      <hr>
      <h3>INPUT CONVENTIONS</h3>
      <div class="description2"><strong>Display Constants</strong>
        <div class="table">
            <table width="707">
               <tr>
                  <td width="58" align="left" valign="top">-</td>
                  <td width="637" align="left" valign="top"><em>[dash associated with the content of subfield $v,
                                                      $x, $y, and $z]</em></td>
               </tr>
          </table>
        </div>Dash (-) that precedes a subdivision in an extended 600 subject heading is not carried
                     in the MARC record. It may be system generated as a display constant associated with the
                     content of subfield $v, $x, $y, and $z.
         <div class="example">
            <table width="100%">
               <tr>
                  <td valign="top" width="5%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
